def calculate_string_value(s: str) -> int:
    alpha = ''
    res = 0
    for c in s:
        x1 = int('@' < c and '[' > c)
        x2 = alpha.index(c.lower()) + 1
        x3 = int('`' < c and '{' > c)
        x4 = x1 * x2
        x5 = x2 * x3
        x6 = x4 - x5
        res += x6
    return res
